Class Frac

  • java.lang.Object
    • Frac

  • public class Frac
extends java.lang.Object
    The Frac class represents fractions (i.e., rational numbers). Frac values are always maintained in normalized form (see reduce() below).
    Author:
    RJ Irwin

      • reduce

        private Frac reduce()
        Normalizes representation of target Frac object. Normalization means adjusting the numerator and denominator to yield an equal value such that:
        • numerator and denominator are reduced to lowest terms
        • only the numerator may be negative (the denominator value will always be non-negative)
        • invalid fractions are stored as 1/0
        • zero-valued fractions are stored as 0/1
        It is important to note that reduce() mutates the target object.
        Returns:
        normalized Frac instance
